Whereas Monsignor Diomartich earned two doctorate degrees theology and church law at the Gregorian
			 University in Rome, Italy, and obtained the title of the lawyer of the
			 Sacra Romana Rota;

Whereas after Monsignor Diomartich came to the United States and served at three parishes in the
			 Archdiocese of New York before he was invited to serve at St. Anthony
			 Croatian Church in Los Angeles, California;

Whereas Monsignor Diomartich's other accomplishments at the parish include the St. Anthony's Annual
			 Picnic Festival, the building of a new rectory, and remodeling and
			 expanding the original parish hall;
